i1.name: Harrier
description: {{sbc|Innate:}} '''Quinn's''' damaging abilities mark enemies with {{as|Vulnerable|gold}}, {{tip|standard sight|revealing}} them for 4 seconds. If no {{as|Vulnerable|gold}} target exists for 1 second, '''{{ci|Valor}}''' automatically marks a nearby visible enemy, which cannot recur for {{pp|type=critical strike chance|color=critical chance|8*(0.99^((x-1)*10))|key1=%|0 to 100 by 10|formula=8*(0.99^critical strike chance %)}} seconds after the mark has timed out, was consumed or was overwritten by another mark.

'''Quinn's''' next [[basic attack]] against a {{as|Vulnerable|gold}} target consumes the mark to deal {{pp|10 to 95|color=physical damage}} {{as|(+ {{pp|key=%|16 to 50}} AD)}} {{as|'''bonus''' physical damage}}.
While {{ai|Behind Enemy Lines|Quinn}} is active, ''Harrier'' is disabled and all {{as|Vulnerable|gold}} marks are removed.
i1.descriptionHtml:
Innate: Quinn's damaging abilities mark enemies with Vulnerable, revealing them for 4 seconds. If no Vulnerable target exists for 1 second, Valor automatically marks a nearby visible enemy, which cannot recur for 0 to 100 by 10 ‒ undefined seconds after the mark has timed out, was consumed or was overwritten by another mark.
Quinn's next basic attack against a Vulnerable target consumes the mark to deal 10 − 95 (based on level) (+ 16% − 50% (based on level) AD) bonus physical damage.
While Quinn's Behind Enemy Lines is active, Harrier is disabled and all Vulnerable marks are removed.
i1.notes:
* If a mark applied by an ability is overwritten, consumed, or timed out, ''Harrier'' goes on a 1-second cooldown if it's not already on cooldown.
* ''Harrier's'' targeting priority:
*# Last unit hit (if it was a small minion it appears to select a different target).
*# Lowest-health enemy champion.
*# Lowest-health enemy minion.
* ''Harrier'' is consumed even if it is parried, the attack is negated in any case.
* ''Harrier'' will not mark enemy {{tip|minions}} while '''Quinn''' is not {{tip|sight|visible}}, but will mark enemy {{tip|champions}}.

q1.name: Blinding_Assault
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Quinn''' sends '''Valor''' in the target direction who stops upon hitting an enemy, marking it as {{ai|Harrier|Quinn|Vulnerable}} and dealing {{as|physical damage}} to all nearby enemies.
If the primary target was a {{tip|champion}}, they become {{tip|nearsight|nearsighted}} for {{fd|1.75}} seconds, otherwise they are {{tip|disarm|disarmed}} instead.
q1.descriptionHtml:
Active: Quinn sends Valor in the target direction who stops upon hitting an enemy, marking it as Quinn's Vulnerable and dealing physical damage to all nearby enemies.
If the primary target was a champion, they become nearsighted for 1.75 seconds, otherwise they are disarmed instead.
q1.notes:
* ''Blinding Assault's'' {{tip|nearsight}} will persist through {{tip|death}}.

e1.name: Vault
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Quinn''' {{tip|dashes}} to the target enemy, dealing {{as|physical damage}}, {{tip|airborne|knocking them back}}, though not through terrain, and {{tip|slow|slowing}} them by 50% decaying over {{fd|1.5}} seconds. She then {{tip|dash|leaps back}} 525 units away from them.
e1.descriptionHtml: Active: Quinn dashes to the target enemy, dealing physical damage, knocking them back, though not through terrain, and slowing them by 50% decaying over 1.5 seconds. She then leaps back 525 units away from them.
e1.notes:
* '''Quinn''' will track the target if they change locations.
** She will dash to the target's previous location without applying ''Vault's'' effects if the target is too far away or moves beyond {{tt|1200|Estimated}} units.
* '''Quinn''' will automatically attempt to attack the target once she completes ''Vault''.
* The target will turn to face the opposite direction after being {{tip|airborne|knocked back}}.
* Unlike its constant cast range ''Vault's'' bounce's can vary to allow '''Quinn''' to close or to make a gap between herself and the target (depending on casting position) or even to jump through a wall (if there is enough landing room on the other side).
* ''Vault'' also interrupts basic attacks with {{tip|uncancellable windup|uncancellable windups}}.{{bug|2}}

r1.name: Behind_Enemy_Lines
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Quinn''' {{tip|channels}} for 2 seconds, signaling '''{{ci|Valor}}''' to pair up. Upon completion, he picks her up and they unite, increasing her {{sti|ms|{{as|{{tt|'''total''' movement speed|Increases base movement as well as bonus movement speed}}}}}}, granting her {{tip|ghosted|ghosting}}, and allowing her to cast ''{{ai|Skystrike|Quinn}}''. ''Behind Enemy Lines'' can be recast after {{fd|0.5}} seconds during the channel.

Taking damage from non-{{tip|minions}} while ''Behind Enemy Lines'' is active or while '''Quinn''' is {{tip|channel|channeling}} causes her to lose the {{as|'''bonus total''' movement speed}} for 3 seconds. Becoming {{tip|immobilize|immobilized}}, {{tip|ground|grounded}}, or {{tip|silence|silenced}} ends ''Behind Enemy Lines'' immediately and puts it on {{sti|cooldown}} without performing ''{{ai|Skystrike|Quinn}}''.
Once ''Behind Enemy Lines'' has been learned, [[death|respawning]] or returning to the [[Spawn|summoning platform]] will spawn '''{{ci|Valor}}''' instantly.
{{sbc|Recast:}} '''Quinn''' cancels the channel, placing ''Behind Enemy Lines'' on cooldown.
r1.descriptionHtml:
Active: Quinn channels for 2 seconds, signaling Valor to pair up. Upon completion, he picks her up and they unite, increasing her total movement speed, granting her ghosting, and allowing her to cast Quinn's Skystrike. Behind Enemy Lines can be recast after 0.5 seconds during the channel.
Taking damage from non-minions while Behind Enemy Lines is active or while Quinn is channeling causes her to lose the bonus total movement speed for 3 seconds. Becoming immobilized, grounded, or silenced ends Behind Enemy Lines immediately and puts it on cooldown without performing Quinn's Skystrike.
Once Behind Enemy Lines has been learned, death or returning to the Spawn will spawn Valor instantly.
Recast: Quinn cancels the channel, placing Behind Enemy Lines on cooldown.
r1.notes:
* Taking damage from non-{{tip|minions}} removes the bonus movement speed buff temporarily by suppressing it with the status effect of a {{tip|slow}}.
* ''Behind Enemy Lines'' does not refund its {{sti|{{as|mana cost}}}} if the channel was canceled via recast.
** The only exception is if '''Quinn's''' {{as|mana}} falls below the {{as|mana cost}}, in which case she is granted enough {{as|mana}} back (the equal amount needed) to be able to cast ''Behind Enemy Lines'' again.
* [[death|Respawning]] or returning to the [[Spawn|summoning platform]] will not spawn '''{{ci|Valor}}''' if ''Behind Enemy Lines'' is on cooldown.
* If '''{{ci|Valor}}''' is spawned by [[death|respawning]] or returning to the [[Spawn|summoning platform]], {{ai|Skystrike|Quinn}} will be disabled from being manually cast for {{fd|2.5}} seconds upon uniting. However, it will still automatically activate upon declaring a [[basic attack]] or casting {{ai|Blinding Assault|Quinn}} or {{ai|Vault|Quinn}}.
* ''Behind Enemy Lines'' ends immediately without {{ai|Skystrike|Quinn}} being cast if she enters or is inside the enemy [[fountain]]. The ability will go on full {{sti|cooldown}}.
** '''Quinn''' will also spawn '''{{ci|Valor}}''' when entering the enemy fountain but she will instantly lose him afterwards.
* Self-{{tip|immobilize|immobilizations}} such as {{ii|Stopwatch}} and {{ii|Zhonya's Hourglass}} also count for ending ''Behind Enemy Lines''.
* The following table refers for interactions while '''Quinn''' is {{tip|channel|channeling}}:
** ''Behind Enemy Lines'' is not a [[Channel#Movement Channels|movement channel]], and so will not be {{tip|interrupt|interrupted}} by {{tip|root}} and {{tip|ground}}.

r2.name: Skystrike
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Quinn''' detaches from '''Valor''', ending {{ais|Behind Enemy Lines|Quinn}} effects and raining arrows down around her, dealing {{as|70% AD}} {{as|physical damage}} to nearby enemies.
Declaring a [[basic attack]] or casting ''{{ai|Blinding Assault|Quinn}}'' or ''{{ai|Vault|Quinn}}'' during ''{{ai|Behind Enemy Lines|Quinn}}'' automatically activates ''Skystrike''.
r2.descriptionHtml:
Active: Quinn detaches from Valor, ending Quinn's Behind Enemy Lines effects and raining arrows down around her, dealing 70% AD physical damage to nearby enemies.
Declaring a basic attack or casting Quinn's Blinding Assault or Quinn's Vault during Quinn's Behind Enemy Lines automatically activates Skystrike.
r2.notes: * If '''Quinn''' uses {{ai|Vault|Quinn}} while {{ai|Behind Enemy Lines|Quinn}} is active, ''Skystrike'' will activate at her target's location after she bounces back.
